National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Preliminary Report
Location:
Fernandina Beach, FL
Accident Number:
WPR18LA132
Date & Time:
05/01/2018, 0845 EDT 
Registration:
N6466
Aircraft:
COSMOS PHASE III
Injuries:
1 Minor, 1 None
Flight Conducted Under:
Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
On May 1, 2018, about 0845 eastern daylight time, a weight-shift-control Cosmos Phase III, 
N6466, sustained substantial damage after it impacted terrain at Fernandina Beach Municipal 
Airport (FHB), Fernandina Beach, Florida. The pilot sustained minor injuries, and the second 
pilot onboard was not injured. The airplane was registered to and operated by the pilot as a 
personal flight under the provisions of 14 
Code of Federal Regulations 
Part 91. Visual 
meteorological conditions prevailed, and no flight plan was filed for the flight that originated at 
0830 from FHB.
In a telephone interview with the National Transportation Safety Board investigator-in-charge, 
the pilot reported that the second pilot was on the controls. During the initial climb, at about 
700 ft above ground level, the airplane suddenly entered a hard left turn. The pilot took control 
of the airplane, but was unable to recover. The airplane impacted terrain in a nose down 
attitude and both pilots were ejected from their seats.
